branchItem.description:
&lt;p&gt;
The use of the DM series, multi-connector, enables panel mount connections with other apparatus and  can provide the reliability of one-touch installation and removal of multi-tubes (nylon, polyurethane).  As a result, separate transportation of panel and machinery equipment and backup unit exchange is made possible. 
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Rectangular multi-connector series KDM has  substantial reduction in mounting space in comparison with a model requiring many union joints for panels and partitions, this model needs only a small space.   KDM is suitable  for use with positive pressure and vacuum.  It is possible to create a multi-connector with mixed tube sizes.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
One-touch fitting manifold series KM has 6 different model options available.  Male  thread and female thread options available on certain models.  Tube material includes nylon, soft nylon and polyurethane.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
The low torque, metal seal, rotary joint series MQR makes it possible to supply air to rotating and sliding components.   Rotational torque is unaffected by supply pressure and temperature fluctuations.  The use of metal seals prevents the spool from  sticking to the rotating surface even after a long period of non- operation. Piping ports are aligned in a spiral line for easy piping.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Series KRM is a flame resistant, one-touch fittings manifold (equivalent to UL-94  standard V-0).  Compact and manifold piping is possible.  There are many varieties (8 different styles) available. 
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Piping module series KB has made distribution easy utilizing one-touch fittings. A locking system makes the use of tools unnecessary for installation of one- touch fittings and makes piping more efficient.   Universal construction allows for changes in air output direction after connections are completed.
&lt;/p&gt;
